# PII and GDPR

Ravo is EU-resident. All data lives in the EU. GDPR is the baseline, not an aspiration.

## What counts as PII here

| Field | Treatment |
|---|---|
| User email (auth identity) | Plaintext; encrypted at rest by Supabase; RLS-enforced |
| Buyer email (from provider webhook) | SHA-256 hashed at ingest; plaintext discarded |
| Display name, avatar, bio | Plaintext; user-controlled; can be anonymized on deletion |
| IBAN, account holder name | Encrypted at rest with pgsodium; RLS-enforced; visible only to org owner/admin and Mollie integration |
| Phone number | If collected: encrypted at rest |
| Buyer name from order | Not collected. The order line stores only ticket type + amount + hashed buyer email |
| IP address | Geo-derived (country, region) at the edge, then truncated to /24 for fraud signal; raw IP never persists |
| Device fingerprint | Hashed UA, OS, browser strings only; no canvas/font fingerprinting |
| Social handles | Plaintext (these are public anyway); user-controlled |

Tag every PII column in DB with `-- @pii` for the export/deletion tooling.

## Lawful basis

| Processing activity | Basis | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Org member auth | Contract | Org's terms with Ravo |
| Ambassador auth | Contract | Ambassador's terms with festival via Ravo |
| Click logging on `go.ravo.fm` | Legitimate interest | Attribution = contractual purpose between festival and ambassador; document this in DPA |
| Buyer email hashing for attribution | Legitimate interest | Hash, not plaintext; used solely for join logic |
| Outbound transactional email | Contract / legitimate interest | Account-related; reward updates etc. |
| Marketing announcements (post-MVP email) | Consent | Opt-in required; one-click unsubscribe |

A DPA template lives in `docs/legal/dpa-template.md` (to be drafted before first paying customer). Festivals sign as data controllers; Ravo is processor.

## Cookies

The redirector sets one first-party cookie:
- Name: `ravo_v` (visitor id)
- Value: opaque random uuid
- HttpOnly: false (needed for client to dedup if it ever runs client-side joins — but currently server-side only, so set HttpOnly: true)
- Secure: true
- SameSite: Lax
- Domain: `.ravo.fm`
- Max-Age: 1 year

This is a functional/strictly-necessary cookie (it fulfills the click the user just initiated). No banner needed for this. The destination site (the ticketing platform) handles their own consent.

In the app itself (admin and ambassador), no third-party tracking cookies. PostHog runs first-party with anonymized identifiers; opt-out available.

## Data subject rights

### Right to access

User clicks "Export my data" in profile settings. An Inngest job:
1. Gathers all rows where `user_id = <id>` or `ambassador_id` joins to the user
2. Includes all `@pii`-tagged columns
3. Produces a JSON file
4. Stores temporarily in Supabase Storage with a 24-hour signed URL
5. Emails the user the link

### Right to erasure (anonymize)

User clicks "Delete my account". A confirmation flow:
1. 7-day grace period (cancelable from email) — prevents impulsive deletion mistakes
2. After grace period, an Inngest job runs `anonymize_user(user_id)`:
   - `users.email` → `deleted_<uuid>@anonymized.ravo.fm`
   - `users.display_name` → `Deleted User`
   - `users.avatar_url` → null
   - `ambassadors.bio` → null, `social_links` → '{}'
   - `ambassador_payout_details` → all encrypted fields → null
   - `email_addresses` → all rows deleted
   - `audit_log` entries: actor_user_id retained (audit integrity), but no joined PII visible
3. Financial records (rewards, payouts, orders, attributions) retain non-identifying references
4. A scheduled purge job (Inngest, runs monthly) deletes anonymized records older than 7 years
5. Audit log entries: `user.deletion_requested`, `user.anonymized`, `user.purged`

Right to erasure does not delete:
- Order records (financial / tax retention)
- Audit log entries (legal / forensic requirement)
- Aggregated/anonymized analytics

### Right to portability

Same as access export, structured JSON.

### Right to rectification

Self-service via profile UI. Org-level corrections (e.g., fixing an attribution) handled in admin with audit log.

## Suppression list

`email_suppressions` is platform-wide. One opt-out applies across all festivals (per ADR-020). Festivals cannot bypass suppression. The list is checked before every outbound email send (both transactional and post-MVP campaigns).

## Provider data handling

Provider webhooks may include buyer emails, names, addresses. Ravo's policy:

- Hash emails at ingest, store hash only
- Discard names, addresses, phone numbers (we don't need them; festival has them via the provider directly)
- Document this in the provider integration code with comments

If a future business requirement forces us to retain buyer plaintext (e.g., a refund-handling flow that emails buyers directly), it gets a new ADR and an explicit lawful-basis review.

## Logging and observability

- Sentry: PII filters configured to scrub `email`, `iban`, `account_holder_name`, `phone` fields automatically
- PostHog: identified events use `user_id` only; never `email` or names; opt-out respected
- Application logs: no PII. Log `user_id` and `org_id` only

Lint rule: console.log/error/warn with arguments named `email`, `iban`, `*name*` → CI fails.

## Data residency

- Supabase: EU region (Frankfurt or Dublin)
- Vercel: Frankfurt
- Upstash Redis: EU
- Resend: EU sending region
- Mollie: NL (data stays in EU by default)
- Sentry: EU instance
- PostHog: EU Cloud

No US-region services in the data plane. If a service has only US options, it's not in the stack.

## Subprocessors

Maintain a list at `docs/legal/subprocessors.md`. Update before adding any new vendor that processes personal data on behalf of orgs. Notify orgs 30 days before changes (per standard DPA template).
